Generate a supplier-facing tender synopsis for the SAP PPS Sourcing Project below.

# Target Portal

- portal_name:        {{ template.portal_name }}
- portal_country_code:{{ template.portal_country_code }}
- standard:           {{ template.standard }}
- date_format:        {{ template.date_format }}
- currency_hint:      {{ template.currency_hint }}
- target_language:    {{ target_language }}

# Fixed Section Superset (MUST use exactly these sections, in this order)

You MUST place every field into one of these section ids. Skip an optional
section entirely if none of its fields have SAP data. NEVER invent a new section.

{% for section in template.section_superset -%}
- id="{{ section.id }}"  title="{{ section.title }}"  order={{ section.order }}  required={{ section.required }}
{% endfor %}

# Fixed Field List (MUST fill exactly these fields, in this order per section)

Do NOT invent new fields. Use the exact `label` string given below. Fill `value`
from the SAP field named in `sap_source_hint` (pipe-separated fallbacks). If the
SAP value is empty, use "Not specified" translated into the target language.

{% for f in template.fields -%}
- id="{{ f.portal_field_id }}"  label="{{ f.label }}"  section="{{ f.section_id }}"  type={{ f.data_type }}  sap_hint="{{ f.sap_source_hint }}"  required={{ f.required }}  important={{ f.important }}
{% endfor %}

{% if template.terminology -%}
# Portal Terminology (use in narrative text, NOT in labels)
{% for k, v in template.terminology.items() -%}
- {{ k }} => "{{ v }}"
{% endfor %}
{% endif %}

# SAP Sourcing Project Data

```json
{{ tender_data_json }}
```

# Output Schema

Return ONLY valid JSON with exactly these keys:

```json
{
  "tenderTitle":          "<SourcingProjectName exactly as provided>",
  "executiveSummary":     "<1-2 sentence supplier summary in {{ target_language }}>",
  "portalName":           "{{ template.portal_name }}",
  "portalCountryCode":    "{{ template.portal_country_code }}",
  "portalComplianceNote": "<1-2 sentences in {{ target_language }} on compliance readiness>",
  "supplierFields": [
    {
      "label":           "<exact label from template.fields[].label>",
      "value":           "<SAP value; 'Not specified' in target language if empty>",
      "sapSource":       "<SAP field name actually used>",
      "sectionId":       "<one of the section ids listed above>",
      "portalFieldId":   "<template.fields[].portal_field_id>",
      "important":       <bool from template>
    }
  ],
  "supplierActions": [
    "<imperative action derived from SupplierRegistrationDeadline in {{ target_language }}>",
    "<imperative action derived from BidSubmissionDeadline in {{ target_language }}>",
    "<imperative action derived from BidOpeningDateTime in {{ target_language }}>"
  ],
  "portalMissingFields": [
    { "label": "<template.fields[].label>", "reason": "<why required for {{ template.portal_name }}>" }
  ],
  "missingInformation": ["<empty SAP fields flagged for human review>"],
  "sourceReferences":  ["<SAP field names actually used>"],
  "language":          "{{ target_language }}",
  "templateVersion":   "{{ template.version }}",
  "templateHash":      "{{ template.template_hash }}"
}
```

# Rules for supplierFields

1. There must be one entry per field listed under "Fixed Field List" above.
2. Order MUST match the order in the fixed list (section by section, following the section order).
3. `label` MUST be the exact string from template - do not translate or reword.
4. `sectionId` MUST be one of the section ids from the fixed superset.
5. `portalFieldId` MUST be the portal_field_id from the template.
6. If a required field has no SAP data, put "Not specified" in value AND add an entry to portalMissingFields.
7. Skip fields for optional sections entirely when SAP data is empty (do NOT emit "Not specified" placeholders).

Do NOT hallucinate. Use only values present in the SAP data.